title: For Sale:  SPF - Kel-Tec P-11 - Stainless Steel - Hard to Find - 99.9999%+ Reliable
location: Brentwood / N. Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
FS: Kel-Tec P-11 - Stainless Steel - Hard to Find - 99.9999%+ Reliable

Especially desirable model... and yes an expensive example of a P-11.

SS slide.  Only offered for a short period way back in the day.  Hard to find. I've not seen another one anywhere.

Won't get dinged up, scratched, rusted, or otherwise likely to show it's age under the harshest of carry conditions.  Looks pretty much the same as the day I acquired it new.

Original hard case, manual, spare SS factory mag.  Note that certain S&W Mod 59 Series mags are compatible.  Lots of accessories available from KT.

Sorted. Really Sorted... 99.9999%+ reliable.  Takes a lot of time between cleanings and a lot of pocket lint to slow it down; just enough to give one a heads up. Quick brushing, a little CLP and back to a full service provider.

Very accurate for short barrel if you do your job.  Which isn't simple being a DAO. On a sand bag it groups and hits POA with the best.

My carry gun for some time.  Won't find a more reliable auto.  Hundreds of rounds - one premature lock back very early on; fixed.  I *think* there was ONE failure to feed in there somewhere and it was the ammo or mag lips a tad off.

New non-SS ones go for $200 to $250, some $300.  Fact: New ones aren't sorted and as great as K-Ts are, initially they frequently need a bit of attention to some details QA missed.  Had other K-Ts and follow online forums so very familiar with issues and their unsurpassed service.  One that works...  it's like money in the bank, er... make that under the mattress.

That's why I'm asking $350.  Firm.

Not satisfied with it, return in same condition as it left and I'll refund the $350 purchase price only; not to include all other expenses.

Only getting rid of it because I don't get to the range enough to stay adequately proficient.  Hate to give it up.

Accept Cash or USPS MO only.

FTF, In-state preferred.

Will consider shipping to buyer's FFL dealer.  Buyer assumes cost of all shipping, handling, FFL transfers, and any other fees involved. Normal paperwork, etc for Person to Person transfers Instate; i.e. a Pistol Permit or CHP in NC.

title: For Sale:  Vintage Daisy SoftAir Tec-9 Replica Airsoft Gun, New Old Stock!!
postcontent:
This was the beginning of the Airsoft craze!! Get a piece of history!!

For sale is a New Old Stock, Daisy Model 12 SoftAir gun, a replica of the Tec-9 handgun.

These were the first airsoft guns brought into the US and were made back in 1987-88 and only sold for 1 year until they were pulled from stores because of how much they resemble the real guns (kids where being held at gunpoint by police officers because of the realism of these replicas). Since this all airsoft guns now require permenant orange tips on the barrel ends or must be a non-gun color, to distinguish "toys" from real firearms.

These airsoft guns fire standard airsoft bb's HOWEVER the bb's are loaded into lifesize 9mm shells and are loaded into an actual magazine! You pump the gun, the bb shoots out and the shell ejects, just like a real gun.
This is a very high quality item, metal and plastic parts and originally sold for $70 back in the 80's!

The gun for sale is as mint as you are going to ever find one. This is New Old Stock, never removed from the box, still has the zip-tie holding the bolt forward, all the shells, targets, manual, sling, bb's, and everything it originally came with. 99% condition, the other 1% is light shelf wear on the box, which will happen to any item sitting on a store shelf.

Asking $130 cash.
Will ship for $10.
Cash, money order, or paypal (+4%).

Call 920--450-3093 if I dont answer please leave me a message.

The newest addition to the Heckler & Koch handgun line, the P2000 "US" incorporates features of the successful HK USP Compact pistol with the latest innovations of HK engineers. This unique pre-cocked hammer system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull and short trigger travel from first to last round fired) with a double action hammer system. The P2000 trigger pull has been reduced to 7.5 to 8.5 pounds of pressure, compared to 9.5 to 11.5 pounds found on many conventional double action pistols.
Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation—one that prevents unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third pull of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the P2000. The enhanced LEM trigger system combines the reliability of a double action revolver trigger with the crisp, precise trigger of a single action pistol. A set of simple-to-install modular grips allows the P2000 to be custom-fitted to any shooter's hand. An ambidextrous magazine release and dual slide release levers make handling the P2000 natural and easy for right- and left-handed shooters alike.
New for HK is the addition of industry standard mounting rails to the P2000 US, allowing the widest variety of lights, laser aimers, and accessories to be added by sliding them onto the open rail system. The HK P2000 US includes the same recurved, hook trigger guard found on the USP Compact and uses reliable and widely available USP Compact magazines.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Bushmaster Assault Rifle, very rare firearm
postcontent:
this is a rifle made by Bushmaster they called the "Assault rifle". its design is a cross between an AK47 and an M16. it is gas piston operated using an M16 bolt. It was built from M16 parts when it was still legal to do that, it has an M16 barrel, bolt, fire control group, pistol grip and uses standard M16/AR15 magazines(4 included). it was built using full auto parts, the sear is now removed of course, and still has the 3 way switch that switches to full auto, thoug hit does not engage anything. These are very hard to find, especially the one with the folding stock. the fore end is wood that was factory painted black. this particular rifle has a strong, smooth action and fires great. the bore looks great as well as the bolt face, this has not been fired much. the grooves and lands of the rifling are strong and shiny. The rifle breaks down much like the M16/AR series of rifles. there are not any videos, that i could find, of this rifle on the internet, or instructions on how to field strip it, it is pretty simple and i will be more than happy to show anyone interested how to do everything on it. i will include a few pictures and have many detailed pictures if you want more. email me with questions and/or offers, serious inquiries only please, i dont want to show it off to a bunch of people just becasue theyve never seen one. keep in mind this is a very rare collectable firearm and ITS VALUE WILL ONLY GO UP. im in no hurry to get rid of it as i really like it, just the only rifle i have in 5.56 and i try to keep the different round types minimal. title: For Sale:  Military 3/4 trailer with tilt
postcontent:
U.S. Military ¾ ton trailer.  Was originally green and now it’s desert tan on the outside.  Very well built heavy duty trailer.  Comes with side rails and rear gate (easily removed).  This trailer has the option of tilting by removing two pins (bolts) in the front where it attaches to the frame, then you set the pair of parking brakes to lock the wheels, then just back your truck up and the whole bed tilts up.  Found that to be a nice feature when doing some major yard work back in the fall.  This can be pulled behind any full size pick up truck.  I don’ t know what it weighs, but it’s not as heavy as you would think.  I pull it behind a dodge 1500 4wd with a tired drivetrain and it does just fine.   

 Overall condition is pretty good.  It’s got some surface rust in the bed and the front wall is a little bent up, I guess is wasn’t soldier proof ?  The wooden/metal rails are in fine working order and should last a good long time.  The 24volt military wiring harness is still there, however the taillights are not.  It is very easy to mount a new set of L.E.D. trailer lights on this trailer, the kit runs about $50.00 from autozone.  Tires are load range D and are like new.
I don’t have a title to it, but I can give you a bill of sale.  I was told that there are certain restrictions about selling these overseas, so I will only sell locally.
Please don’t email me with stupid questions, in fact, don’t email me at all.   Just call, it’s a lot easier for me. REDACTED

No, I don’t want to trade, don’t need any help selling it and I really am not interested in what you think it’s worth and how cheap your buddy sold one.  I really don’t care.  I’m located in Summerville SC and don’t really plan on selling it to some idiot in Indiana who may or may not drive down this summer to pick it up.  If you want it, come and pay for it.  Sorry for sounding like a jerk, but there are a ton of idiots our there.

Here are all the dimensions I figured I might need to write down.
Overall length:  149”  That’s from the Lunette ring to the last protruding lift ring
Overall width:  73”  That’s from the outside of each tire
Interior bed length: 95.5 with tailgate closed

Interior bed width otherwise is 65”
